cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation and labeling tasks. The use of ensemble strong classifiers and the proposed DMT architecture also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of Bayesian Networks and Structured Random Forests also indicates that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of medical images with lesions suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
